Description: Copper alloy amulet in the form of an wedjat-eye, pierced lengthwise.
Curator's comments: The Museum register indicates a general reference to the small bronze finds mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 (§ 80), where the item is not clearly described.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.59, p.179, pl.21)
